In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November as National Family Caregivers Month. He acknowledges the important role that caregivers play in the healthcare system and expresses gratitude for their selfless work. He highlights the support available to caregivers through programs like the Affordable Care Act and Medicaid. The article also mentions the Caregivers and Veterans Omnibus Health Services Act, which provides assistance to the caregivers of injured veterans. President Obama emphasizes the need for appreciation and flexibility in the healthcare system, workplaces, and communities to support caregivers. He encourages all Americans to recognize and honor those who care for their loved ones.